dcterms:creator: Y. Randall
T. Treibitz
dcterms:description: The FLSea dataset features forward looking imagery close to the sea floor in relatively shallow water depths less than 10 m. It consists of 22,451 image frames with RGB and metric ground truth depth data at 12 different underwater locations, showcasing various lighting challenges such as reflections, turbidity, and attenuation.
dcterms:title: FLSea

dcterms:creator: G. Billings
R. Camilli
M. Johnson-Roberson
dcterms:description: The LizardIsland dataset consists of a stereo image sequence collected with a downward facing diver operated camera rig conducting a survey of a coral reef. It includes 2,216 sequential images processed to obtain ground truth dense depth maps and optimized feature maps for input into the network.
dcterms:title: LizardIsland Dataset
